apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) Two people were killed and five were injured as Cyprus was jolted by its strongest earthquake in 42 years. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 The tremors Thursday night were also felt across the Mediterranean in Lebanon and northern Israel. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 On the island of Cyprus, 24 villages in the the Troodos mountain range were affected, the government said. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 In one, Arodhes, a town of several hundred people, most of the homes collapsed. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Villagers fled into the streets and many spent the night in cars as up to 30 aftershocks joggled the ground and landslides covered mountain roads. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Charilaos Hadjigeorghiou, 73, and his wife, Stella, 65, were crushed to death in their bed when their home collapsed in the village of Miliou, 55 kilometers (35 miles) west of the capital, Nicosia. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 The quake struck at 11:02 p.m. (2002 GMT). 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Government chief seismologist Kyriacos Solomis said it had a preliminary magnitude of 5.2. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 A quake of magnitude 5 can cause considerable damage. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 A major quake in the same area of western Cyprus killed dozens in 1953. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 There were no immediate reports of injuries or damage in Lebanon or Israel. 
